messages.text: just leave me alone, whoever you are
Why are you being like this
What are you up to right now?
Why aren’t you out with the boys??
look, whoever this is you need to stop.
You don’t sound surprised to hear from me.
I’ve been missing for a week
The cops have had no luck
I disappeared, as they say, without a trace
I’ve always been a little crazy.
Like maybe I’m in New York City now or something.
You know exactly where I am.
Remember the last time you saw me?
We went as a group. You. Me. Chelsea. Stefan. Josh. Sara.
You were wearing that dumb purple tie
Anyway we all had a blast on the ride there.
She was wearing that AMAZING dress. She looked so glamorous.
I don’t really remember what she was wearing.
Like I said, I was wasted.
Not too wasted to slow dance with me
It was the first time we’d really spent time together since our breakup
What song were we dancing to, again?
Right. You do remember SOMETHING, then.
Yeah, I guess, now that you mention it.
So we’re dancing. And you take me by the hand and we walk out of the auditorium. It was so cold that night.
There was a winter storm warning but everything was so still right then.
Next thing I know we’re talking in Stefan’s dad’s car. Having a heart-to-heart.
You said that you thought I was cute but you’d gotten over me and were in love with Josh.
We drove up to the Lookout.
Where are you now? Everyone is really worried.
If you were that worried you would have called the police by now
And shown them this exchange we’re having.
What makes you think I didn’t?
Because you aren’t so in control of your sanity
You are, after all, involved in a text message conversation with your ex.
That’s enough to put anyone on edge
But texting with your DEAD ex girlfriend—that’s just crazy. Like mental institution crazy.
Let’s go back to that night again, shall we?
There was this annoying song on the radio, I remember.
I told you to turn it off but you wouldn’t.
You turned it up louder and started singing along and dancing.
I just wanted you to shut up. I was so pissed at you for what you’d said earlier.
It was like you were TRYING to hurt me.
I put my hands around your neck
Pushed you in. You floated away
The ice storm came the next day and the lake froze.
You know they’ll find me when it melts.
I drove back to the dance.
Stayed out with Chelsea and Josh and Stefan and Sara til 1 or 2am.
You’re crying right now, aren’t you.
I’m a ghost. I know these things.
Oh god Veronica. I’m so sorry.
I didn’t mean for it to happen like that.
When you throw your ex into a freezing lake
Make sure her phone goes down with her
Make sure her best friend doesn’t find it in the back of Stefan’s dad’s car and start texting her best friend’s ex from said phone a week later
I’ve been holding on to V’s phone because I KNEW there was something wrong when I found it in the car that night. She couldn’t go 3 minutes without it.
Because if anyone’s BUSTED right now, it’s you.
Or is it about your little confession??
Anyway, I’m sure the police will love to hear your side of things, especially after I show them our convo.
